summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling previous relevant resolutions and statements on Yemen, 
Reaffirming commitment to Yemen's unity, sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity, 
Determining the situation in Yemen remains a threat to international peace and security, 
Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter, 
1. Renews until 15 November 2025 measures imposed by paragraphs 11 and 15 of resolution 2140 (2014), reaffirming provisions of paragraphs 12, 13, 14, and 16 of resolution 2140 (2014) and paragraphs 14 to 17 of resolution 2216 (2015); 
2. Extends until 15 December 2025 the mandate of the Panel of Experts, with intention to review and take action by 15 November 2025, and requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Panel, in consultation with the Committee; 
3. Requests the Panel of Experts to provide a midterm update by 15 April 2025 and a final report by 15 October 2025 to the Security Council; 
4. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
